This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with person re-identification, which is a common task in computer vision. The use of deep learning models and adversarial learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of GANs and image generation techniques could also suggest that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the focus on security and the potential for attacks on person re-identification systems could suggest that it could belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
